<lb/><p rend="right">2 March 1865</p><!-- printed embossed address on paper <p rend="right"><placeName rend="Newstead Abbey, Nottinghamshire, originally an Augustinian priory founded by Henry II in about 1170. It was the home of the poet Lord Byron and sold by him in 1818. In 1861, it was purchased by William Frederick Webb (1829-1899), a big-game hunter, who Livingstone had met in 1850. Livingstone stayed at Newstead Abbey in 1864-65. (C&amp;C 249">NEWSTEAD ABBEY</placeName>,</p>
<p rend="right"><placeName>MANSFIELD.</placeName>.</p>
<p rend="right"><placeName>NOTTS.</placeName> <lb/></p>--><!--end of printed address-->
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName ref="#d1e65">Sir John</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I thank you 
<lb/>very much for kindly 
<lb/>writing about the 
<lb/>trees in the <choice><sic>Artic</sic><corr>Arctic</corr></choice>
<lb/>regions putting 
<lb/>forth fresh leaves 
<lb/>while the roots 
<lb/>are still hard frozen. 
<lb/>This putting forth 
<lb/>of new buds &amp; 
<lb/>leaves while the 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002213_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'-->
<lb/>the roots can draw 
<lb/>no moisture is the 
<lb/>only part to which 
<lb/>I refer - but as it 
<lb/>is not essential 
<lb/>to the statement 
<lb/>that your name 
<lb/>be mentioned I 
<lb/>shall omit it. 
<lb/>I did not like to 
<lb/>mention your 
<lb/>name without 
<lb/>letting you know 
<lb/>beforehand.</p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002213_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'-->
<lb/><p>We had begun to 
<lb/>think in this 
<lb/>quarter that the 
<lb/><choice><sic>Artic</sic><corr>Arctic</corr></choice> climate had 
<lb/>come thus far 
<lb/>south - didn't 
<lb/>actually blame 
<lb/>the Admiralty 
<lb/>for some mistake 
<lb/>in the gulph 
<lb/>stream but 
<lb/>thought the 
<lb/>weather atrocious</p>
<lb/><p>I hope you have 
<lb/>been enjoying 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002213_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'-->
<lb/><!-- MJH - changed to '4' from '3' --> good health through 
<lb/>it all and am 
<lb/>very Truly Yours</p>
<lb/><p><persName>David <surname>Livingstone</surname></persName></p>
<lb/><p>To</p>
<lb/><p><persName ref="#d1e189">Sir John <surname>Richardson</surname></persName></p>
			
</div>
